Note:
XML Emitter

Buffer management delegated to the shared byte-buffer foundation
in emitter_common.runa. XML-specific helpers for entity-escaped text
and attribute emission are preserved.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as MemoryCore

@Reasoning:
Typed handle for the XML backend; the entity-escape methods are the
critical XML-specific behavior that cannot live in EmitterCommon.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three fields shadow the raw EmitterCommon byte buffer.
@End Implementation

Type called "XMLEmitter":
    buffer as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    length as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Factory entry hiding EmitterCommon from the XML backend.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_xml_emitter" returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lifecycle pair for create_xml_emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope:
Caller must guarantee the handle is live and not already destroyed.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_xml_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Pre-sizing hook for large documents.
@End Reasoning

Process called "ensure_buffer_space" takes emitter as Integer, required_space as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity from EmitterCommon with emitter, required_space
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-byte primitive for XML structural characters (<, >, /, =, "',
spaces).
@End Reasoning

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(1) amortized.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bulk emission for element names, attribute names, and pre-escaped text.
Callers must pre-escape; use emit_escaped_text for raw user content.
@End Reasoning

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(n) in input length.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Input is emitted verbatim. Caller is responsible for ensuring the string
contains no characters that require XML entity escaping. For untrusted
text content use emit_escaped_text instead.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
End Process

@Reasoning:
Text-node content in XML must escape '&', '<', and '>' to preserve
well-formedness (W3C XML 1.0, Section 2.4). This helper performs that
escaping in a single linear pass so callers never have to remember
which characters need entities.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the input string byte-by-byte. For '&' (38) emits "&amp;", for
'<' (60) emits "&lt;", for '>' (62) emits "&gt;". All other bytes are
emitted verbatim. Returns 0 on null emitter or null string, 1 on success.
The '>' case is technically only required after "]]" but is escaped
unconditionally for safety, matching common XML libraries.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) in input length with one branch per character. Hot path for
content-heavy XML output.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Designed for untrusted text content; produces well-formed XML for any
byte sequence so long as the input is valid UTF-8. Does not validate
UTF-8 itself; callers are responsible for encoding validity.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "emit_escaped_text" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit string with XML text-content escaping for &, <, >.
    If emitter is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let str_length be proc string_length from StringCore with str
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than str_length:
        Let char be proc memory_get_byte from MemoryCore with str, index

        If char is equal to 38:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&amp;"
        Otherwise:
            If char is equal to 60:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&lt;"
            Otherwise:
                If char is equal to 62:
                    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&gt;"
                Otherwise:
                    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
XML attribute values have a stricter escaping rule than text content:
in addition to '&', '<', '>', they must also escape the quote character
used to delimit the value. We escape both '"' and "'" so the same
escaped string can be safely wrapped in either delimiter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the input byte-by-byte. Emits "&amp;" for 38, "&lt;" for 60,
"&gt;" for 62, "&quot;" for 34, "&apos;" for 39. All other bytes are
emitted verbatim. Returns 0 on null emitter or null string, 1 on success.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) in input length with at most five branch tests per character.
Hot path for attribute-heavy XML output.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Designed for untrusted attribute values; produces well-formed XML for
any byte sequence so long as the input is valid UTF-8.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "emit_escaped_attribute" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit string with XML attribute-value escaping for &, <, >, ", '.
    If emitter is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let str_length be proc string_length from StringCore with str
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than str_length:
        Let char be proc memory_get_byte from MemoryCore with str, index

        If char is equal to 38:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&amp;"
        Otherwise:
            If char is equal to 60:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&lt;"
            Otherwise:
                If char is equal to 62:
                    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&gt;"
                Otherwise:
                    If char is equal to 34:
                        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&quot;"
                    Otherwise:
                        If char is equal to 39:
                            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "&apos;"
                        Otherwise:
                            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated XML document for the driver.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope:
Returned pointer aliases the emitter's internal buffer; do not free
directly and do not use after destroy_xml_emitter.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_output" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Exposes current byte count for golden-output diff tools.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_output_length" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_length from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lets the driver reuse a single emitter across multiple XML documents.
@End Reasoning

Process called "reset_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_reset from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process
